t: Praise*p ye the Lord.*s Praise ye the Lord*s from the heavens: praise him in the heights.
Praise*p ye him, all his angels: praise ye him, all his hosts.
Praise*p ye him, sun and moon: praise him, all ye stars of light.
Praise*p him, ye heavens of heavens, and ye waters that be above the heavens.
Let*p them praise the name of the Lord:*s for he commanded, and they were created.
He*p hath also stablished them for ever and ever: he hath made a decree which shall not pass.
Praise*p the Lord*s from the earth, ye dragons, and all deeps:
Fire,*p and hail; snow, and vapour; stormy wind fulfilling his word:
Mountains,*p and all hills; fruitful trees, and all cedars:
Beasts,*p and all cattle; creeping things, and flying fowl:
Kings*p of the earth, and all people; princes, and all judges of the earth:
Both*p young men, and maidens; old men, and children:
Let*p them praise the name of the Lord:*s for his name alone is excellent; his glory is above the earth and heaven.
He*p also exalteth the horn of his people, the praise of all his saints; even of the children of Israel, a people near unto him. Praise ye the Lord.*s
